    </div>
    <div class="advice">
        <h2>How to Safeguard Your Online Accounts</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>Never click on links or download attachments from unknown or suspicious sources.</li>
            <li>Be cautious of emails that appear to come from well-known companies but use generic email addresses.</li>
            <li>Use strong, unique passwords for each of your accounts.</li>
            <li>Enable two-factor authentication (2FA) whenever possible to add an extra layer of security.</li>
            <li>Be wary of emails that contain urgent calls to action or threaten consequences if you don’t act immediately.</li>
            <li>Keep your software and systems up to date to protect against the latest threats.</li>
        </ul>
    </div>
</body>
</html>
```

This HTML message provides a clear alert about phishing attempts and offers practical advice to help recipients protect their online accounts.

